  <meta property="og:description" content="Mitigating Bias in Machine Learning discusses how practicing model developers, might build fairer predictive systems and avoid causing harm (sometimes that might mean not building something at all). Part I offers context (philosophical, legal, technical) and practical solutions. Part II discusses how we quantify different notions of fairness. Part III analyses methods for mitigating bias through model interventions.">
